# Git Identity Manager — Cursor Rules

## Project
Zero-dependency, pure Bash TUI/CLI tool (v1.1.0) for managing multiple Git identities.
Single entry point: `git-manager.sh`. Do NOT create additional script files.
Language: Bash only. No npm, pip, gem, cargo, or any external runtime.

## Runtime Paths
- `~/.git-manager/profiles/<nickname>` → profile (pure `git config` commands)
- `~/.ssh/git-manager.d/<nickname>.conf` → isolated SSH Host block per identity
- `~/.ssh/id_ed25519_<nickname>` → generated SSH private key
- `~/.ssh/config` → NEVER write directly; `Include` bootstrap is injected at startup only
- `~/.bashrc` / `~/.zshrc` → aliases: `as-<nick>` (local) and `as-<nick>-global`

## Script Variables
```bash
VERSION="1.1.0"
MANAGER_DIR="$HOME/.git-manager"
PROFILES_DIR="$MANAGER_DIR/profiles"
SSH_CONF_DIR="$HOME/.ssh/git-manager.d"
SHELL_PROFILE   # ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc (auto-detected)
CLI_MODE        # "true" = CLI; "" = TUI/interactive
profiles=()     # Array populated by get_profiles()
```

## Functions
| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `get_profiles()` | Fills `profiles[]` array from `PROFILES_DIR` |
| `setup_identity()` | Generates new SSH ed25519 + GPG keys |
| `import_identity()` | Links existing SSH/GPG keys to a profile |
| `finalize_profile()` | Writes profile, SSH conf, and shell aliases |
| `switch_identity($profile, $scope)` | Applies profile locally or globally |
| `view_profiles()` | Tabular listing of all profiles |
| `modify_identity()` | Updates name/email of a profile |
| `delete_identity()` | Removes profile and associated files |
| `print_keys()` | Shows SSH/GPG public keys for a profile |
| `run_doctor()` | Auto-fixes permissions, configs, and aliases |
| `check_for_updates()` | Checks and applies updates from GitHub |
| `print_help()` | Prints CLI usage text |
| `quick_guide()` | In-TUI how-to guide |

## CLI Interface
```
git-manager setup               # Generate keys + create profile
git-manager import              # Link existing SSH/GPG keys
git-manager switch <profile>    # Apply profile locally
git-manager global <profile>    # Apply profile globally
git-manager view                # List all profiles
git-manager doctor              # Health check + auto-fix
git-manager update              # Force update check
git-manager --help              # Show help
```

## Rules
1. All code lives in `git-manager.sh`. Never split into multiple files.
2. Every new function must be registered in BOTH:
   - `case "$1" in` CLI argument parser (bottom of file)
   - `while true; do` TUI main menu loop (bottom of file)
3. Interactive functions must:
   - Start with `clear`
   - End with `[[ -z "$CLI_MODE" ]] && read -p " Press Enter to return to the menu..."`
4. Message prefixes: `[?]` prompt · `[i]` info · `[+]` success · `[!]` error · `[*]` status
5. Every SSH conf block written to `~/.ssh/git-manager.d/` MUST contain `IdentitiesOnly yes`
6. Profile files contain ONLY `git config` commands — no secrets, no key material

## Prohibited
- No external package dependencies of any kind
- No splitting `git-manager.sh` into multiple files
- No direct writes to `~/.ssh/config`
- No SSH private key content or passwords stored in files
- No languages other than Bash
